ome.smuggler.core.msg

Interface RepeatConsumer<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ImportFinaliser, ImportProcessor, MailProcessor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BatchCompletedHandler, BatchDisposalHandler, BatchUpdateHandler, Finaliser, ImportRunner, Mailer

    public interface RepeatConsumer<T>
    Plugs into a channel sink to consume its data and optionally request that the same data be delivered again. Use in conjunction with MessageRepeater or OnceOffSchedule and OnceOffRepeatConsumer.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      RepeatAction consume(T data)
      Consumes the message data and returns an indication of whether the same data should be delivered again.

    • Method Detail

      • consume

        RepeatAction consume(T data)
        Consumes the message data and returns an indication of whether the same data should be delivered again.
        Parameters:
        data - the data received from the channel.
        Returns:
        either Repeat to indicate the data should be delivered again or Stop to indicate no further action should be taken.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null.
